#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.152"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.152:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.152:0.2"
msgid "15. Diṭṭhivagga"
msgstr "15. Views"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 152. Soattāsutta → eso attā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.152:0.3"
msgid "152. Soattāsutta"
msgstr "152. This Is My Self"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.183"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.152:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.152:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi "
"uppajjati:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on "
"what, does the view arise:"

msgctxt "sn22.152:1.3"
msgid ""
"‘so attā, so loko, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato "
"avipariṇāmadhammo’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After passing away I will be "
"permanent, everlasting, eternal, and imperishable’?”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:1.4"
msgid "Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …."
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:1.5"
msgid ""
"“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi "
"uppajjati:"
msgstr ""
"“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view "
"arises:"

msgctxt "sn22.152:1.6"
msgid ""
"‘so attā, so loko, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato "
"avipariṇāmadhammo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After passing away I will be "
"permanent, everlasting, eternal, and imperishable.’"

msgctxt "sn22.152:1.7"
msgid "Vedanāya … pe …"
msgstr "When feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.152:1.8"
msgid "saññāya …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.152:1.9"
msgid "saṅkhāresu … pe …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.152:1.10"
msgid ""
"viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:"
msgstr ""
"consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on "
"consciousness, the view arises:"

msgctxt "sn22.152:1.11"
msgid ""
"‘so attā, so loko, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato "
"avipariṇāmadhammo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After passing away I will be "
"permanent, everlasting, eternal, and imperishable.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.152:2.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.5"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.6"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi "
"uppajjeyya:"
msgstr ""
"“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would "
"the view arise:"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.7"
msgid ""
"‘so attā, so loko, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato "
"avipariṇāmadhammo’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After passing away I will be "
"permanent, everlasting, eternal, and imperishable’?”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.9"
msgid "“Vedanā …"
msgstr "“Is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.10"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.11"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.12"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.13"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.14"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.15"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.16"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi "
"uppajjeyya:"
msgstr ""
"“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would "
"the view arise:"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.17"
msgid ""
"‘so attā so loko, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato "
"avipariṇāmadhammo’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After passing away I will be "
"permanent, everlasting, eternal, and imperishable’?”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.18"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.19"
msgid "“Evaṃ passaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "“Seeing this …"

msgctxt "sn22.152:2.20"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti."
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.152:2.21"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
